{
  "stem": "24466.7",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Kasman, what you told me, you told me about-- about Kaufman, a brother Kaufman, that was working in tanneries.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "She said, yes, yes, yes.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Hm.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Tomorrow I am arranging that you will be in that and that flat-- the address he gave her, [INAUDIBLE] with my cousin, one of my cousins.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Your brother will pick you up tomorrow from there.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I took from Lublin.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "He came and told me the whole story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He gave me the address where he is, where he find her, after two and 1/2 years being in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And [pauses] he gave me the address.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I took a Jeep with one of the Russian officers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Went-- the war was going on.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I went through [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] places that, from both sides, they were shooting, and everything was in fire, you know.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "It was about 5:00 in the morning, I think, to Krakow-- from Lublin to Krakow-- got the address.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "She opened the door, and that was when I-- when I was find my sister.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "Being in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "I'm talking about the time when I was in Lublin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was-- what I can tell you?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't recognize her.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because after so many years, to be over two years-- two and 1/2 years in-- in-- in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] She was sent there with a court order in 1940.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "No, '40-- sorry. 1941, if I don't-- I would like to make it-- I can't tell you exactly.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "With a court order as a political prisoner to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Auschwitz was built as a prisoner.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "To [INAUDIBLE] not as a Jewess, a prisoner, as a-- as a-- no, how to call this.",
      "word_count": 17
    }
  ],
